      BS
   =20
 =20
Uh, I don=E2=80=99t know, here=E2=80=99s a paper:What is the effect of seem=
ingly impressive verbal financial assertions that are presented as true and=
 meaningful but are actually meaningless; that is, financial pseudo-profoun=
d bullshit? We develop and validate a novel measurement scale to assess con=
sumers=E2=80=99 ability to detect and distinguish financial bullshit. We sh=
ow that this financial bullshit scale captures a unique construct that is o=
nly moderately correlated with related constructs such as financial knowled=
ge, numeracy, and cognitive reflection. Consumers particular vulnerable to =
financial bullshit are more likely to be young, male, have a higher income,=
 and be overconfident with regards to their own financial knowledge. The ab=
ility to detect and distinguish financial bullshit also predicts financial =
well-being while being less predictive of consumers=E2=80=99 self-reported =
financial behavior, suggesting that susceptibility to financial bullshit is=
 linked to affective rather than behavioral reactions.They basically survey=
ed people online and asked them to rate the =E2=80=9Cmeaningfulness=E2=80=
=9D of aphorisms about finance, some of them =E2=80=9Cgenerated by searchin=
g for actual quotes related to the financial domain=E2=80=9D and others gen=
erated =E2=80=9Cby using bullshit generators like www.makebullshit.com.=E2=
=80=9D People who rated the =E2=80=9Cfake=E2=80=9D ones higher than the =E2=
=80=9Creal=E2=80=9D ones were more likely to be young, male and overconfide=
nt, though honestly even Googling real quotes about finance is not necessar=
ily the best way to order your affairs.=C2=A0The real profound=C2=A0stateme=
nts include:Every time you borrow money, you are robbing your future self. =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0Nathan W. MorrisInflation is taxation without legislation. =
=E2=80=94=C2=A0Milton FriedmanWealth is not his that has it, but his that e=
njoys it. =E2=80=94=C2=A0Benjamin FranklinSure.=C2=A0The fake pseudo-profou=
nd ones include:Money eases the costs of those who borrow.Good investors sp=
read large shares beyond size.Freedom and space transform the abstract mean=
ing of money.I kind of like the fake ones? Money really does ease the costs=
 of those who borrow!
